<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-04-25T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-04-25T00:00:00-05:00" n="120" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d120">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">Marshall Mission Files, Lot 54–D270</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Memorandum by General <persName type="from">Shang
                                    Cheng</persName><note n="56" xml:id="d120fn56">Chief of the
                                    Department of Military Protocol, Chinese National Military
                                    Council.</note> to General <persName type="to">Marshall</persName></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 86</seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Chungking</hi></placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-04-25">25 April 1946</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Reference is made to your memo of 21 April relating to the equipping and
                            training of ten divisions of Communist troops.</p>
                        <p>I have the pleasure to inform you that the memorandum was handed down to
                            this Department by His Excellency, The Generalissimo, with the following
                            note: <quote rend="blockquote">
                                <p>“As the matter concerns the reorganization of the Communist
                                    forces, I would like to confer with General Marshall and examine
                                    it before decisions should be made.”</p>
                            </quote></p>
                        <closer>For <signed> General Shang Cheng <lb/>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Yu Chi-shi</hi>
                            </signed><lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Chief of Bureau of Military Affairs</hi></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>